main event: An unidentified flying object was reported at Gander AFB in Newfoundland on March 23, 1958, observed via ground radar and air visual for 1.5 hours.
interesting points: The object moved southeast at a slow speed of 150 mph and made sharp 90-degree turns., Multiple conclusions suggested the object could possibly be a balloon, aircraft, or astronomical phenomenon., No concrete identification was made due to insufficient data., Observations also included a sighting of a cigar-shaped object by an AGC crew member., The object was visually described as flashing, maneuvering, and changing direction rapidly.
witness description: Air Force personnel and AGC crew members
